# GNOME Shell extensions from extensions.gnome.org (e.g.o).
# User-level (~/.local/share/gnome-shell/extensions) — installed + enabled by
# profiles/workstation/06z-gnome-extensions.sh. Hand-maintained (NOT generated
# by capture/; the apt snapshot can't see e.g.o-installed extensions — which is
# exactly why these were lost on the last fresh box).
#
# Format: uuid [@group]   — @group gates on that apt group's host-conf toggle;
# no @group = always (desktop baseline). Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# WAYLAND NOTE: a freshly INSTALLED extension cannot be loaded into a running
# Wayland session — the phase installs + flags it enabled, but it only becomes
# ACTIVE after the next log out / log in. Already-installed ones enable live.
#
# Distro extensions (ubuntu-dock, appindicators, ding, tiling-assistant) ship
# with the desktop — do NOT list them here; they're managed by GNOME/Ubuntu.

clipboard-history@alexsaveau.dev    # Clipboard History — searchable clipboard manager (Wayland-fine)
monitor@astraext.github.io          # Astra Monitor — top-bar system monitor (Wayland-native; replaces the
                                    #   unmaintained system-monitor-next@paradoxxx.zero from the old box)
